 When the going gets tough, they struggle.

59
00:02:27,160 --> 00:02:28,760
 And you see, it's interesting for us,

60
00:02:28,760 --> 00:02:30,600
 because as we're going to look through this series,

61
00:02:30,600 --> 00:02:32,640
 don't give the enemy a seat at your table.

62
00:02:32,640 --> 00:02:35,440
 It's focusing on Psalm 23.

63
00:02:35,440 --> 00:02:37,920
 And you all probably know Psalm 23.

64
00:02:37,920 --> 00:02:41,080
 It's probably the most famous passage of scripture, right?

65
00:02:41,080 --> 00:02:42,760
 But I wanted to ask you another question.

66
00:02:42,760 --> 00:02:47,480
 If I was to boil down what Psalm 23 is really about,

67
00:02:47,480 --> 00:02:49,160
 what would you say it's about?

68
00:02:49,160 --> 00:02:52,200
 The Lord is my shepherd, and I will dwell in the house

69
00:02:52,200 --> 00:02:53,040
 of the Lord forever.

70
00:02:53,040 --> 00:02:54,120
 What's it really about?

71
00:02:54,120 --> 00:02:57,440
 This short chapter, the most famous chapter of six verses,

72
00:02:57,440 --> 00:02:58,880
 what's it really about?

73
00:02:58,880 --> 00:03:02,000
 I think it's about how you face challenges,

74
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:03,360
 how you respond.

75
00:03:03,360 --> 00:03:05,720
 They often say, it's not really what happens to you

76
00:03:05,720 --> 00:03:08,320
 that matters, it's how you respond, right?

77
00:03:08,320 --> 00:03:11,440
 In some ways, Psalm 23, which I'm trying to find here,

78
00:03:11,440 --> 00:03:12,560
 is about that.

79
00:03:12,560 --> 00:03:15,080
 It's about how we respond to challenges.

80
00:03:15,080 --> 00:03:18,760
 It's about how much we trust in God,

81
00:03:18,760 --> 00:03:20,560
 and how much we trust in the truth.

82
00:03:20,560 --> 00:03:23,720
 That's why truth and trust are so similar.

83
00:03:23,720 --> 00:03:28,120
 How much do we trust in God is what Psalm 23 is about.

84
00:03:28,120 --> 00:03:29,280
 And I wanted to go through this

85
00:03:29,280 --> 00:03:31,680
 because it's very important as we look at

86
00:03:31,680 --> 00:03:34,520
 how we don't give the enemy a seat at the table.

87
00:03:34,520 --> 00:03:36,640
 It really comes down to how tight

88
00:03:36,640 --> 00:03:38,480
 are we holding on to truth?

89
00:03:38,480 --> 00:03:41,360
 You see, one thing that is for sure,

90
00:03:41,360 --> 00:03:43,640
 if we invite the enemy to our table,

91
00:03:43,640 --> 00:03:45,880
 he really wants to bring about our destruction.

92
00:03:45,880 --> 00:03:47,880
 That's his purpose, that's his goal.

93
00:03:47,880 --> 00:03:50,040
 And how does he often do that?

94
00:03:50,040 --> 00:03:53,240
 Through deceit, through lies,

95
00:03:53,240 --> 00:03:56,320
 through the very thing against truth.

96
00:03:56,320 --> 00:03:57,400
 That's how he does it.

97
00:03:57,400 --> 00:03:59,640
 He wants to tell you, he wants you to feel

98
00:03:59,640 --> 00:04:02,080
 that you have no value, that you have no worth,

99
00:04:02,080 --> 00:04:04,640
 that you have no purpose, that no one loves you.

100
00:04:04,640 --> 00:04:08,240
 Nicky Gumbel often shares a story that's been in my head,

101
00:04:08,240 --> 00:04:10,360
 and I'm paraphrasing it 'cause I don't remember all of it,

102
00:04:10,360 --> 00:04:12,480
 but he's telling this imaginary story

103
00:04:12,480 --> 00:04:15,720
 of the devil talking to his demons,

104
00:04:15,720 --> 00:04:18,520
 and they're scheming on how to distract

105
00:04:18,520 --> 00:04:20,360
 the people of earth from God.

106
00:04:20,360 --> 00:04:23,040
 And they're like, "Oh, what about if we feed them the lie

107
00:04:23,040 --> 00:04:26,080
 "that all they need is money, sex, and power?"

108
00:04:26,080 --> 00:04:27,120
 And he's like, "No, no, no,

109
00:04:27,120 --> 00:04:28,440
 "because at some point they'll find out.

110
00:04:28,440 --> 00:04:29,920
 "At some point, as they go down this road,

111
00:04:29,920 --> 00:04:32,280
 "they'll realize that that doesn't fulfill."

112
00:04:32,280 --> 00:04:33,960
 And fast forward to the end, he says,

113
00:04:33,960 --> 00:04:36,600
 "The best lie that we can tell them

114
00:04:36,600 --> 00:04:38,400
 "is that there is no hurry,

115
00:04:38,400 --> 00:04:43,560
 "that there may be a God, that he really may love you,

116
00:04:43,560 --> 00:04:44,920
 "that you really should follow him,

117
00:04:44,920 --> 00:04:47,720
 "but the lie is there's no hurry.

118
00:04:47,720 --> 00:04:50,800
 "Let's feed them the lie that there is no hurry,

119
00:04:50,800 --> 00:04:53,120
 "that they can put it back to tomorrow.

120
00:04:53,120 --> 00:04:55,520
 "Maybe that's the most dangerous lie."

121
00:04:55,520 --> 00:04:58,160
 So how are we supposed to face these kinds of lies?

122
00:04:58,160 --> 00:05:00,000
 How are we supposed to face this kind of deceit?

123
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:03,440
 By looking at the word of God, by looking at the truth.

124
00:05:03,440 --> 00:05:05,600
 And I would say in the whole of scripture,

125
00:05:05,600 --> 00:05:08,280
 Psalm 23 is probably the most powerful,

126
00:05:08,280 --> 00:05:11,160
 most potent, most appropriate passage

127
00:05:11,160 --> 00:05:13,760
 for how you respond to challenges,

128
00:05:13,760 --> 00:05:15,640
 how you face the enemy.

129
00:05:15,640 --> 00:05:18,680
 Because in Ephesians chapter six,

130
00:05:18,680 --> 00:05:20,600
 Paul talks about the whole armor of God.

131
00:05:20,600 --> 00:05:22,360
 And what's the sword of the spirit?

132
00:05:22,360 --> 00:05:24,000
 It's the word of God.

133
00:05:24,000 --> 00:05:28,120
 So the question really is, how well do we know Psalm 23?

134
00:05:28,120 --> 00:05:29,560
 Those of us who have been in the church for a long time

135
00:05:29,560 --> 00:05:32,160
 will have sang songs about Psalm 23, right?

136
00:05:32,160 --> 00:05:34,160
 How well do we know?

137
00:05:34,160 --> 00:05:36,520
 Do we know it off by heart?

138
00:05:36,520 --> 00:05:38,840
 Do we know it in our hearts?

139
00:05:38,840 --> 00:05:40,520
 And I wanted to read it to you first.

140
00:05:40,520 --> 00:05:42,760
 I want to just recite it to you,

141
00:05:42,760 --> 00:05:44,280
 but I want you to think about this.

142
00:05:44,280 --> 00:05:48,680
 When David is writing this passage, these six verses,

143
00:05:48,680 --> 00:05:50,800
 what is he really saying?

144
00:05:50,800 --> 00:05:52,920
 What does he want us to know?

145
00:05:52,920 --> 00:05:56,760
 When he says, "The Lord is my shepherd, I shall not want.

146
00:05:56,760 --> 00:05:58,880
 He makes me lie in green pastures.

147
00:05:58,880 --> 00:06:01,200
 He leads me beside still waters.

148
00:06:01,200 --> 00:06:04,520
 He restores my soul.

149
00:06:04,520 --> 00:06:09,520
 He leads me in paths of righteousness for his name's sake.

150
00:06:09,520 --> 00:06:10,880
 Even though I walk through the valley

151
00:06:10,880 --> 00:06:13,800
 of the shadow of death, I will fear no evil

152
00:06:13,800 --> 00:06:16,480
 for you are with me, your rod and your staff,

153
00:06:16,480 --> 00:06:17,480
 they comfort me.

154
00:06:18,480 --> 00:06:22,520
 You prepare a table before me in the presence of my enemies.

155
00:06:22,520 --> 00:06:26,720
 You anoint my head with oil and my cup overflows.

156
00:06:26,720 --> 00:06:29,640
 Surely, goodness and mercy will follow me

157
00:06:29,640 --> 00:06:32,280
 all the days of my life, and I shall dwell

158
00:06:32,280 --> 00:06:34,720
 in the house of the Lord forever."

159
00:06:34,720 --> 00:06:37,600
 That is the word of God.

160
00:06:37,600 --> 00:06:40,400
 That is the truth that we should be following.

161
00:06:40,400 --> 00:06:42,720
 That is the truth that we should be remembering

162
00:06:42,720 --> 00:06:44,800
 in our hearts, living it.

163
00:06:44,800 --> 00:06:46,120
 Psalm 23 is an interesting one,

164
00:06:46,120 --> 00:06:48,400
 'cause where do you hear about Psalm 23 the most?

165
00:06:48,400 --> 00:06:50,720
 Where do you hear it read the most?

166
00:06:50,720 --> 00:06:55,720
 Funerals, 'cause it's always associated with death, right?

167
00:06:55,720 --> 00:06:58,560
 Dying, it's the encouragement for everyone.

168
00:06:58,560 --> 00:07:00,280
 But what I want to propose to you today,

169
00:07:00,280 --> 00:07:01,600
 what I want to present to you today

170
00:07:01,600 --> 00:07:04,480
 is it isn't really just about death.

171
00:07:04,480 --> 00:07:07,920
 In fact, it's much more about living than you realize.

172
00:07:07,920 --> 00:07:11,240
 Confession to make, John last week when he was sharing,

173
00:07:11,240 --> 00:07:13,440
 he gave you all a preview saying,

174
00:07:13,440 --> 00:07:17,320
 "James is gonna present a Psalm 23 remix."

175
00:07:17,320 --> 00:07:19,840
 And I was listening to that bit, and I was like,

176
00:07:19,840 --> 00:07:23,800
 "Oh, I am," 'cause I hadn't written the sermon at that time,

177
00:07:23,800 --> 00:07:27,360
 and I suddenly was wondering what kind of remix should I do?

178
00:07:27,360 --> 00:07:29,360
 You definitely don't want to hear me rap.

179
00:07:29,360 --> 00:07:32,480
 That's a definite no-no.

180
00:07:32,480 --> 00:07:33,320
 - Oh, come on.

181
00:07:33,320 --> 00:07:36,840
 (audience laughing)

182
00:07:36,840 --> 00:07:38,440
 - And then I thought, you know what?

183
00:07:38,440 --> 00:07:39,520
 And I was like, "God, please tell me.

184
00:07:39,520 --> 00:07:41,960
 Please tell me how to make this kind of interesting

185
00:07:41,960 --> 00:07:43,080
 for all these brothers and sisters

186
00:07:43,080 --> 00:07:45,440
 who probably know this passage very well."

187
00:07:45,480 --> 00:07:47,520
 And then it occurred to me,

188
00:07:47,520 --> 00:07:49,480
 if we're talking about not giving the enemy

189
00:07:49,480 --> 00:07:52,200
 a seat at the table, what if we did?

190
00:07:52,200 --> 00:07:54,600
 What if we did let the enemy sit here?

191
00:07:54,600 --> 00:07:56,920
 And what if we did believe in his lies?

192
00:07:56,920 --> 00:08:00,080
 What if we let him distort this truth?

193
00:08:00,080 --> 00:08:02,800
 I want to present to you the, well, I just recited

194
00:08:02,800 --> 00:08:04,440
 the Lord is my shepherd in the ESV,

195
00:08:04,440 --> 00:08:05,360
 the English Standard Version,

196
00:08:05,360 --> 00:08:07,560
 but I wanted to present to you a different version today

197
00:08:07,560 --> 00:08:11,520
 in parallel, which is the ERV, the Enemy Remixed Version.

198
00:08:11,520 --> 00:08:13,640
 And this is what it is.

199
00:08:13,640 --> 00:08:17,560
 I want to show you the real scripture, the real truth,

200
00:08:17,560 --> 00:08:21,240
 but when you compare it to what I have imagined.

201
00:08:21,240 --> 00:08:25,160
 Now, disclaimer, I wrote it myself, okay?

202
00:08:25,160 --> 00:08:27,760
 But it was me asking, "James, what would happen

203
00:08:27,760 --> 00:08:30,520
 if I let the enemy have a seat at my table?

204
00:08:30,520 --> 00:08:33,720
 How would he distort this scripture?

205
00:08:33,720 --> 00:08:35,760
 And how would it make me feel?"

206
00:08:35,760 --> 00:08:37,240
 So this is my own interpretation.

207
00:08:37,240 --> 00:08:38,880
 I'm not the most creative kind of person.

208
00:08:38,880 --> 00:08:40,480
 And I welcome you to go back

209
00:08:40,480 --> 00:08:42,920
 and maybe you can rewrite your own one,

210
00:08:42,920 --> 00:08:44,200
 your own Remixed Version,

211
00:08:44,200 --> 00:08:45,400
 because I think it's very important.

212
00:08:45,400 --> 00:08:46,960
 It really helped me.

213
00:08:46,960 --> 00:08:48,040
 So I want to go through each verse.

214
00:08:48,040 --> 00:08:50,560
 There's only six, and I want to really go through them.

215
00:08:50,560 --> 00:08:51,880
 The first verse, of course, is,

216
00:08:51,880 --> 00:08:55,000
 "The Lord is my shepherd, I shall not want."

217
00:08:55,000 --> 00:08:57,520
 John, last week, emphasized the word my.

218
00:08:57,520 --> 00:08:59,400
 The Lord is my shepherd.

219
00:08:59,400 --> 00:09:02,280
 There's this intimacy that comes with it.

220
00:09:02,280 --> 00:09:03,200
 He's mine.

221
00:09:03,200 --> 00:09:04,040
 He knows me.

222
00:09:04,040 --> 00:09:04,880
 He cares for me.

223
00:09:04,880 --> 00:09:07,840
 It's actually a really interesting way,

224
00:09:07,840 --> 00:09:10,720
 a good way to meditate, if those of you who are learning

225
00:09:10,720 --> 00:09:13,720
 and struggling, is taking a sentence such as that,

226
00:09:13,720 --> 00:09:17,160
 "The Lord is my shepherd," and emphasizing different words,

227
00:09:17,160 --> 00:09:19,040
 and spending time emphasizing different words.

228
00:09:19,040 --> 00:09:20,560
 So the Lord is my shepherd.

229
00:09:20,560 --> 00:09:22,280
 Jesus is my shepherd.

230
00:09:22,280 --> 00:09:24,440
 The Lord is my shepherd.

231
00:09:24,440 --> 00:09:25,960
 The Lord is my shepherd.

232
00:09:25,960 --> 00:09:29,400
 Actually, David would have very well known

233
00:09:29,400 --> 00:09:31,200
 what a shepherd had to do.

234
00:09:31,200 --> 00:09:33,040
 He was a shepherd boy himself.

235
00:09:33,040 --> 00:09:34,720
 But actually, back in those days,

236
00:09:34,720 --> 00:09:36,120
 for someone who was reading that,

237
00:09:36,120 --> 00:09:38,480
 shepherd actually had an even stronger connotation,

238
00:09:38,480 --> 00:09:39,800
 which was king.

239
00:09:39,800 --> 00:09:42,400
 Someone who had authority over something.

240
00:09:42,400 --> 00:09:45,600
 Someone who cared for something, a leader.

241
00:09:45,600 --> 00:09:46,720
 So what David is saying here is,

242
00:09:46,720 --> 00:09:47,920
 "The Lord is my shepherd.

243
00:09:47,920 --> 00:09:49,440
 "He is my king.

244
00:09:49,440 --> 00:09:50,400
 "He knows me.

245
00:09:50,400 --> 00:09:52,080
 "He cares for me.

246
00:09:52,080 --> 00:09:53,240
 "And he looks after me.

247
00:09:53,240 --> 00:09:56,200
 "And I shall not want.

248
00:09:56,200 --> 00:09:59,560
 "And I shall not want."

249
00:09:59,560 --> 00:10:01,440
 But what if you imagined if this was done

250
00:10:01,440 --> 00:10:04,040
 in a remixed version, and it comes up here?

251
00:10:04,040 --> 00:10:07,880
 If I was to flip it and translate it,

252
00:10:07,880 --> 00:10:11,160
 if I was to invite the enemy to come and distort this truth,

253
00:10:11,160 --> 00:10:12,520
 it would sound something like this.

254
00:10:12,520 --> 00:10:14,640
 I have no one to lead me.

255
00:10:14,640 --> 00:10:16,680
 No one who cares.

256
00:10:16,680 --> 00:10:19,360
 Nothing ever seems enough.

257
00:10:19,360 --> 00:10:21,200
 And as I present these parallels to you,

258
00:10:21,200 --> 00:10:24,840
 I want you to think, which one do you resonate more with?

259
00:10:24,840 --> 00:10:27,000
 Which one do you believe more with?

260
00:10:27,000 --> 00:10:30,080
 Now, maybe in your head, you should believe the real one,

261
00:10:30,080 --> 00:10:31,240
