00:26:40,120 --> 00:26:44,560
 But both tools require close proximity.

666
00:26:44,560 --> 00:26:47,240
 So he's saying, "I won't have to fear

667
00:26:47,240 --> 00:26:50,560
 "as I walk through this because Jesus, you,

668
00:26:50,560 --> 00:26:53,560
 "my good shepherd, you are with me.

669
00:26:53,560 --> 00:26:58,640
 "And your rod and your staff, they deliver me."

670
00:26:58,640 --> 00:27:02,920
 No, they help me escape.

671
00:27:02,920 --> 00:27:07,160
 No, "Your rod and your staff, they comfort me."

672
00:27:07,160 --> 00:27:11,480
 So we see here, no promise of immunity,

673
00:27:11,480 --> 00:27:13,880
 no promise of deliverance.

674
00:27:13,880 --> 00:27:16,520
 He's saying that in your trials, in your suffering,

675
00:27:16,520 --> 00:27:18,400
 whatever you're going through right now,

676
00:27:18,400 --> 00:27:23,400
 Jesus is with you to comfort you, to get through this.

677
00:27:23,400 --> 00:27:26,720
 And Romans talks about this because it's in the suffering

678
00:27:26,720 --> 00:27:29,000
 that you will then persevere,

679
00:27:29,000 --> 00:27:31,960
 and then you'll gain character, and then you'll have hope.

680
00:27:31,960 --> 00:27:35,880
 So he is with you.

681
00:27:35,880 --> 00:27:37,240
 And really the crux of this,

682
00:27:37,240 --> 00:27:39,880
 the key point of this verse is this.

683
00:27:39,880 --> 00:27:43,680
 "Even though I will, even though I walk

684
00:27:43,680 --> 00:27:45,400
 "through the valley of the shadow of death,

685
00:27:45,400 --> 00:27:47,360
 "I will fear no evil."

686
00:27:48,200 --> 00:27:49,040
 That's it.

